03e\"}]},{\"section\":\"synonyms\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.synonyms\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"books.Synonyms\",\"title\":\"synonyms\",\"id\":2197,\"bb\":1946,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/b1946/\",\"shadow_value\":\"\u003cem\u003edaivī\u003c/em\u003e – transcendental; \u003cem\u003ehi\u003c/em\u003e – certainly; \u003cem\u003eeṣā\u003c/em\u003e – this; \u003cem\u003eguṇa-mayī\u003c/em\u003e – consisting of the three modes of material nature; \u003cem\u003emama\u003c/em\u003e – My; \u003cem\u003emāyā\u003c/em\u003e – energy; \u003cem\u003eduratyayā\u003c/em\u003e – very difficult to overcome; \u003cem\u003emām\u003c/em\u003e – unto Me; \u003cem\u003eeva\u003c/em\u003e – certainly; \u003cem\u003eye\u003c/em\u003e – those who; \u003cem\u003eprapadyante\u003c/em\u003e – surrender; \u003cem\u003emāyām etām\u003c/em\u003e – this illusory energy; \u003cem\u003etaranti\u003c/em\u003e – overcome; \u003cem\u003ete\u003c/em\u003e – they.\",\"word_for_word_value\":[{\"word\":\"daivī\",\"translation\":\"transcendental\"},{\"word\":\"hi\",\"translation\":\"certainly\"},{\"word\":\"eṣā\",\"translation\":\"this\"},{\"word\":\"guṇa-mayī\",\"translation\":\"consisting of the three modes of material nature\"},{\"word\":\"mama\",\"translation\":\"My\"},{\"word\":\"māyā\",\"translation\":\"energy\"},{\"word\":\"duratyayā\",\"translation\":\"very difficult to overcome\"},{\"word\":\"mām\",\"translation\":\"unto Me\"},{\"word\":\"eva\",\"translation\":\"certainly\"},{\"word\":\"ye\",\"translation\":\"those who\"},{\"word\":\"prapadyante\",\"translation\":\"surrender\"},{\"word\":\"māyām etām\",\"translation\":\"this illusory energy\"},{\"word\":\"taranti\",\"translation\":\"overcome\"},{\"word\":\"te\",\"translation\":\"they\"}]}]},{\"section\":\"translation\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.translation\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"translation\",\"id\":2198,\"bb\":1947,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/b1947/\",\"body_value\":\"This divine energy of Mine, consisting of the three modes of material nature, is difficult to overcome. But those who have surrendered unto Me can easily cross beyond it.\"}]},{\"section\":\"purport\",\"section_title\":\"Books.Verse.purport\",\"children\":[{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2199,\"bb\":1948,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/b1948/\",\"body_value\":\"$3b\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2200,\"bb\":1949,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/b1949/\",\"body_value\":\"Another meaning of \u003cem\u003eguṇa\u003c/em\u003e is rope; it is to be understood that the conditioned soul is tightly tied by the ropes of illusion. A man bound by the hands and feet cannot free himself – he must be helped by a person who is unbound. Because the bound cannot help the bound, the rescuer must be liberated. Therefore, only Lord Kṛṣṇa, or His bona fide representative the spiritual master, can release the conditioned soul. Without such superior help, one cannot be freed from the bondage of material nature. Devotional service, or Kṛṣṇa consciousness, can help one gain such release. Kṛṣṇa, being the Lord of the illusory energy, can order this insurmountable energy to release the conditioned soul. He orders this release out of His causeless mercy on the surrendered soul and out of His paternal affection for the living entity, who is originally a beloved son of the Lord. Therefore surrender unto the lotus feet of the Lord is the only means to get free from the clutches of the stringent material nature.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2201,\"bb\":1950,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/14/b1950/\",\"body_value\":\"The words \u003cem\u003emām eva\u003c/em\u003e are also significant. \u003cem\u003eMām\u003c/em\u003e means unto Kṛṣṇa (Viṣṇu) only, and not Brahmā or Śiva. Although Brahmā and Śiva are greatly elevated and are almost on the level of Viṣṇu, it is not possible for such incarnations of \u003cem\u003erajo-guṇa\u003c/em\u003e (passion) and \u003cem\u003etamo-guṇa\u003c/em\u003e (ignorance) to release the conditioned soul from the clutches of \u003cem\u003emāyā.\u003c/em\u003e In other words, both Brahmā and Śiva are also under the influence of \u003cem\u003emāyā.\u003c/em\u003e Only Viṣṇu is the master of \u003cem\u003emāyā;\u003c/em\u003e therefore He alone can give release to the conditioned soul. The \u003cem\u003eVedas\u003c/em\u003e (\u003cem\u003eŚvetāśvatara Upaniṣad\u003c/em\u003e 3.8) confirm this in the phrase \u003cem\u003etam eva viditvā,\u003c/em\u003e or “Freedom is possible only by understanding Kṛṣṇa.” Even Lord Śiva affirms that liberation can be achieved only by the mercy of Viṣṇu. Lord Śiva says, \u003cem\u003emukti-pradātā sarveṣāṁ viṣṇur eva na saṁśayaḥ:\u003c/em\u003e “There is no doubt that Viṣṇu is the deliverer of liberation for everyone.”\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 7.14\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 7.14\"},{\"id\":2202,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"15\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 15\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/advanced-view/#bb1951\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Dansk (Danish)\",\"language_code\":\"da\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/da/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Deutsch (German)\",\"language_code\":\"de\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/de/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"English\",\"language_code\":\"en\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Español (Spanish)\",\"language_code\":\"es\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/es/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Eesti keel (Estonian)\",\"language_code\":\"et\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/et/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Suomen kieli (Finnish)\",\"language_code\":\"fi\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/fi/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Français (French)\",\"language_code\":\"fr\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/fr/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Hrvatski (Croatian)\",\"language_code\":\"hr\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/hr/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Magyar (Hungarian)\",\"language_code\":\"hu\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/hu/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"한국어 (Korean)\",\"language_code\":\"ko\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/ko/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Lietuvių kalba (Lithuanian)\",\"language_code\":\"lt\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/lt/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Nederlands (Dutch)\",\"language_code\":\"nl\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/nl/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Polski (Polish)\",\"language_code\":\"pl\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/pl/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Português (Portuguese)\",\"language_code\":\"pt-br\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/pt-br/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Русский (Russian)\",\"language_code\":\"ru\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/ru/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Slovenčina (Slovak)\",\"language_code\":\"sk\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/sk/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Slovenščina (Slovenian)\",\"language_code\":\"sl\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/sl/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"українська мова (Ukrainian)\",\"language_code\":\"uk\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/uk/library/bg/7/15/\"},{\"display_name\":\"isiZulu (Zulu)\",\"language_code\":\"zu\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/zu/\"}],\"breadcrumb\":[{\"url_path\":\"/en/library/\",\"title\":\"Library\"},{\"url_path\":