impure devotees who engage themselves in the transcendental service of the Lord achieve their respective goals, and by the grace of the Supreme Lord, when they are fully Kṛṣṇa conscious, they actually enjoy spiritual association with the Supreme Lord. But those who are worshipers of demigods never reach the Supreme Lord in His supreme planet. Even the less intelligent Brahman-realized persons cannot reach the supreme planet of Kṛṣṇa known as Goloka Vṛndāvana. Only persons who perform activities in Kṛṣṇa consciousness (\u003cem\u003emām āśritya\u003c/em\u003e) are actually entitled to be called Brahman, because they are actually endeavoring to reach the Kṛṣṇa planet. Such persons have no misgivings about Kṛṣṇa, and thus they are factually Brahman.\"},{\"type\":\"content.Record\",\"title\":\"paragraph\",\"id\":2340,\"bb\":2074,\"url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/29/b2074/\",\"body_value\":\"Those who are engaged in worshiping the form or \u003cem\u003earcā\u003c/em\u003e of the Lord, or who are engaged in meditation on the Lord simply for liberation from material bondage, also know, by the grace of the Lord, the purports of Brahman, \u003cem\u003eadhibhūta,\u003c/em\u003e etc., as explained by the Lord in the next chapter.\"}]}],\"short_title\":\"Bg. 7.29\",\"medium_title\":\"Bhagavad-gītā As It Is 7.29\"},{\"id\":2341,\"meta\":{\"type\":\"books.Verse\",\"slug\":\"30\",\"show_in_menus\":false,\"seo_title\":\"\",\"search_description\":\"\",\"first_published_at\":null,\"alias_of\":null,\"locale\":\"en\"},\"title\":\"TEXT 30\",\"advanced_view_url_path\":\"/en/library/bg/7/advanced-view/#bb2075\",\"language_menu\":[{\"display_name\":\"አማርኛ (Ethiopian)\",\"language_code\":\"am\",\"enabled\":false,\"url_path\":\"/am/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Български (Bulgarian)\",\"language_code\":\"bg\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/bg/library/bg/7/30/\"},{\"display_name\":\"Čeština (Czech)\",\"language_code\":\"cs\",\"enabled\":true,\"url_path\":\"/cs/library/bg/7/30/\"},{\"display_name\":