 the son of Devakī and Vasudeva, or a prince, or a powerful living entity. This is also condemned in the \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"11\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/bg/9/11/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhagavad-gītā\"}],\" (9.11)\"]}],\". \",[\"$\",\"em\",\"13\",{\"children\":\"Avajānanti māṁ mūḍhā mānuṣīṁ tanum āśritam:\"}],\" “Only the fools regard Me as an ordinary person.”\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L4d\",\"child-2298\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:23:child_items:4:children:4\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"children\":[\"The fact is that no one can understand Kṛṣṇa without rendering devotional service and without developing Kṛṣṇa consciousness. The \",[\"$\",\"$L29\",\"1\",{\"href\":\"/en/library/sb/10/14/29/\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"em\",\"0\",{\"children\":\"Bhāgavatam\"}],\" (10.14.29)\"]}],\" confirms this:\"]}]}],[\"$\",\"$L4d\",\"child-2299\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:23:child_items:4:children:5\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base text-center italic\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"\u003cem\u003eathāpi te deva padāmbuja-dvaya-\u003cbr /\u003eprasāda-leśānugṛhīta eva hi\u003cbr /\u003ejānāti tattvaṁ bhagavan-mahimno\u003cbr /\u003ena cānya eko ’pi ciraṁ vicinvan\u003c/em\u003e\"}}]}],[\"$\",\"$L4d\",\"child-2300\",{\"child\":\"$2b:props:children:0:props:children:props:page:child_items:0:children:23:child_items:4:children:6\",\"hasId\":true,\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"em:mb-4 em:leading-8 em:text-base s-justify\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"“My Lord, if one is favored by even a slight trace of the mercy of Your lotus feet, he can understand the greatness of Your personality. But those who speculate to understand the Supreme Personality of Godhead are una